## Completed! ✓

I've successfully completed the TDD exercise for Conway's Game of Life:

**Test Coverage (16 tests, all passing):**
- ✅ Rule 1: Underpopulation (cells with <2 neighbors die)
- ✅ Rule 2: Survival (cells with 2-3 neighbors survive)
- ✅ Rule 3: Overpopulation (cells with >3 neighbors die)
- ✅ Rule 4: Reproduction (dead cells with exactly 3 neighbors become alive)
- ✅ Blinker pattern (oscillating vertical/horizontal line)
- ✅ Block pattern (stable 2×2 square)
- ✅ Single cell dies
- ✅ Negative coordinates (both x and y)
- ✅ Empty grid handling

**Implementation:**
- `src/game-of-life.ts`: Efficient sparse representation using a Set to track living cells, only checking cells that could potentially change (living cells + their neighbors)
- Correctly handles infinite grids with positive and negative coordinates
- All Game of Life rules properly implemented
